title: Basketball Recap: Carrollwood Day Takes a Loss
text:
Carrollwood Day was the 64-57 winner over Tampa Prep when they last played one another back in February of 2023, but their luck changed this time around. The Carrollwood Day Patriots took a blow against the Tampa Prep Terrapins on Thursday, falling 74-46. While losing is never fun, the Patriots can't take it too hard given the team's big disadvantage in MaxPreps' Florida basketball rankings (they are ranked 245th, while the Terrapins are ranked 81st).
Patriots
Previous 5 Games
With the defeat, Carrollwood Day broke their four-game winning streak and moved their record to 14-11. As for Tampa Prep, their victory was their 16th straight at home, which pushed their record up to 21-2.
Both are set to take part in some playoff action in their next matches. Carrollwood Day will square off against Seffner Christian at 6:00 p.m. on Monday. As for Tampa Prep, they and Berkeley Prep will face off at 7:00 p.m. on Friday without much rest having both just played. One thing working in Tampa Prep's favor is that they have posted at least 55 points in their last five matches.
